  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA302-kiḷavi">itu paruvaṅ kaḻintatu kaṇṭu talaimakaḷ colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said when seeing the season pass.</p>
        </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA302">
<l>          iḻaiyaṇi makaḷiriṉ viḻaitaka pūtta</l>
<l>          nīṭucuri yiṇara cuṭarvīk koṉṟaik</l>
<l>          kāṭukaviṉ pūtta vāyiṉu naṉṟum</l>
<l>          varumaḻaik ketiriya maṇiniṟa virumputa</l>
<l>          ṉarainiṟam paṭutta nalliṇart teṟuḻvī</l>
<l>          tāan tēralar kollō cēynāṭṭuk</l>
<l>          kaḷiṟutait tāṭiya kaviḻka ṇiṭunīṟu</l>
<l>          veḷiṟil kāḻa vēla nīṭiya</l>
<l>          paḻaṅkaṇ mutuneṟi maṟaikkum</l>
<l>          vaḻaṅkaruṅ kāṉa miṟantici ṉōrē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent">Although they have [already] flowered</l>
<l rend="indent2">– the beauty of the wilderness –</l>
<l rend="indent2">he Laburnum trees with glowing blossoms in long curly clusters</l>
<l rend="indent2">that flowered to evoke desire like jewel-adorned women,</l>
<l>doesn’t he make out</l>
<l rend="indent2">the Teṟuḻ blossoms in good clusters that turned to white colour</l>
<l rend="indent2">on the sapphire-coloured big bushes in the face of the abundantly</l>
<l rend="indent2">coming rain,</l>
<l>– he who traversed the forest difficult to wander,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the distressful old path, overgrown with Vēlam trees</l>
<l rend="indent2">with cores without whiteness, is concealed, by the dust</l>
<l rend="indent2">from<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">kaviḻ kaṇ iṭu nīṟu</term>: the verbal root <term xml:lang="ta">iṭu</term> seems to function here as a sort of ablative conjunction, similar perhaps to <term xml:lang="ta">koṇṭu</term> for an instumental ("with"); cf. two parallels with <term xml:lang="ta">kaḷari</term> instead of <term xml:lang="ta">kaṇ</term> in NA 41.2 (where transmission seems to favour <term xml:lang="ta">viṭu</term> over <term xml:lang="ta">iṭu</term>) and 126.3.</note> the upturned area in which the elephant had bathed,</l>
<l rend="indent2">kicking [it], in a distant land?</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
